result.name: Japanese Restaurant Doraya

reviews.text: Decent price for lunch set, with self-served salad. Friendly staff and well cooked Japanese cuisine. Recommended by my friend and I don’t regret having an unforgettable meal there. Why not give it a try? It’s pretty crowdy and busy in lunch hours, so better get there when they just open up.
food quality is good and portion is also large. Buffet salad is good with many options

For HKD$135, you get this whole Minced Bluefin Tuna Bowl Set in Tsim Sha Tsui. I would definitely say it’s a great deal!

The portion of minced bluefin tuna was generous, which was more than enough for me to enjoy each mouthful of rice with some fish. The tuna was fatty and fresh, very delicious indeed!

Not to miss is all the sides! The steamed egg was awesome! Smooth and enjoyable. Miso soup was ordinarily good. And the little dish on the top left hand corner was fantastic! I didn’t know what that was, it’s like some sort of flavored veggie noodles that’s so yum!

I would definitely recommend you to try Doraya if you are in the hood.
Fresh seafood and comfortable casual setting. A break from the hustle and bustle in HK if you go outside of peak hours.
Nice Tuna Steak on top of well seasoned Sushi Rice
